{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XNmzts98XiPkrWJ8LYgyzM","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Comprehensive Project Summary:\n\n1. Directory Structure:\n```\n.\n├── .dockerignore\n├── .mvn/wrapper/maven-wrapper.properties\n├── Dockerfile\n├── mvnw\n├── mvnw.cmd\n├── pom.xml\n└── src/\n    └── main/\n        ├── java/com/example/addressbookspring/\n        │   ├── Application.java\n        │   ├── ServletInitializer.java\n        │   ├── config/\n        │   │   ├── JsfConfig.java\n        │   │   └── SpringConfig.java\n        │   ├── entity/\n        │   │   └── Contact.java\n        │   ├── repo/\n        │   │   └── ContactRepository.java\n        │   ├── service/\n        │   │   └── ContactService.java\n        │   └── web/\n        │       └── ContactController.java\n        └── resources/\n            ├── application.properties\n            ├── Bundle.properties\n            ├── ValidationMessages.properties\n            └── META-INF/\n                ├── faces-config.xml\n                └── resources/\n```\n\n2. Build System: \n- Maven (pom.xml)\n- Java Version: 17\n- Spring Boot Packaging: WAR\n\n3. Spring Version and Dependencies:\n- Spring Core Version: 6.2.11\n- Key Dependencies:\n  - spring-boot-starter-data-jpa\n  - spring-boot-starter-web\n  - spring-boot-starter-validation\n  - jsf-spring-boot-starter (JoinFaces)\n  - H2 Database (Runtime)\n\n4. Configuration:\n- application.properties highlights:\n  - In-memory H2 database\n  - Development JSF project stage\n  - Server port: 8080\n  - Date format: MM/dd/yyyy\n\n5. Spring-specific Annotations:\n- @Configuration: SpringConfig.java, JsfConfig.java\n- @Service: ContactService\n- @Repository: ContactRepository\n- @Autowired: Used in ContactController\n- @Bean: Used in JsfConfig\n\n6. Dockerfile Details:\n- Base Image: maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n- Additional setup for Python, uv, and Playwright\n- Build command: `mvn clean package spring-boot:run`\n\n7. Additional Observations:\n- Uses Jakarta Faces (JSF) with Spring Boot\n- Includes XHTML templates in resources\n- Configured with Weld servlet for CDI support\n\nThis is a Spring Boot + JSF address book application with a comprehensive, modern setup leveraging the latest Jakarta and Spring technologies.\n\nWould you like me to dive deeper into any specific aspect of the project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5178e60b-6983-4b64-b8b8-e65cc691e770","uuid":"752c006a-e5e8-4ab4-a9c8-5a21522c1a64"}
